  One of the problems is HOW do you even know if it's a quality part
with-out testing. A good example is pressure plates (200 mm Sachs). These
have been great pressure plates for the last few years as real German ones
went up so high in price they became a deal, but, for the last 6 months
there has been a serious quality issue with them being stamped 1mm to small
in diameter. The general layman mechanic would never notice this, but a true
professional would? 
  I could go on and on about quality issues with all manufacturers. It's a
real pita but parts need to be checked constantly. Ate wheel cylinders, when
there was a shortage they were packaging TVS India as a replacement till
theirs were available again and even those aren't made in Germany anymore.
   If a parts vendor just keeps on selling these (parts) without checking
then there will be a lot of premature worn out engines due to the thrust
bearing wearing out due to un-equal weight.
   Once the word gets out about these everyone who bought one will pull
their engines to check. I personally have already warrentied 3 of these and
have quit selling them till I know they are right.
   Like ALL products sold by me, everything is TEST FIT and time tried
before ever sold to the general public.  It has taken me over 5 years to get
the split bus parts down pat and have been testing bat window parts for a
couple years, 100's maybe 1000's of dollars of bay parts given away to be
tested by drivers in all different climates.

Ronnie   old volks of az
www.type21parts.com

